==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: muted
<hw>muted</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as <er>quiet</er>;
<as>as, the <ex>muted</ex> atmosphere of a church</as>. Opposite of
<ant>noisy</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hushed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>softened; rendered less loud or harsh; -- of sounds
and instruments which produce sounds; <as>as, <ex>muted</ex>
trumpets</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dull, muffled, softened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mute-hill</ent>⟦br⟧
